==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cherimoyer
<hw>Cher`i*moy"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>ch⟦eacute⟧rimolier</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A small downy-leaved tree (<spn>Anona Cherimolia</spn>), with
fragrant flowers. It is a native of Peru.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Its delicious fruit, which is succulent, dark
purple, and similar to the custard apple of the West Indies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cherish</ent>⟦br⟧
